artist: Webb Pierce / Howdy Roberts & WMT Rangers
comment: West Monroe, Louisiana’s Webb Pierce was one of the most popular honky tonk, rockabilly, vocalists, guitarists of the 1950’s, charting more number one hits than any other artist during the decade. He already had more than ten #1 country hits before his first appearance at Danceland – “Slowly”, “There Stands The Glass’, “More And More” and “It’s Been So Long” among them, His hits not only went to # 1 but stayed there for weeks on end. His biggest hit “In The Jailhouse Now”, charted for 37 weeks, 21 of them at number one! The country music superstar makes the first of three appearances this year.
